      <h3>Power Switches</h3>
      <p><strong>Main Power:</strong> Lift the paddle of the start/stop switch at the back of the headstock. Press down to shut off. Remove the yellow lock key when OFF to prevent unwanted use. The machine will not operate without this key.</p>
      <p><strong>E-STOP:</strong> The red emergency stop button is on the front of the headstock. Depress to stop the machine. Twist to reset. Only reset after the emergency has been corrected.</p>
      <p><strong>Start/Stop:</strong> The ON/OFF switch for starting the chuck or a program is at the bottom right of the Control Panel.</p>

      <h3>Motor</h3>
      <p>The drill press is supplied with a 1-1/2 hp, 110V motor contained within the headstock. It drives the quill and chuck through a pulley system.</p>

